<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIT-AND-RUN DRIVER KILLS MAN, 72 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 72-year-old Sylmar man was killed by a hit-and-run driver as he crossed a 
street in San Fernando early Monday morning, San Fernando police said. 
</P>
<P>
Lloyd W. Hurlimann was crossing Hubbard Street near 2nd Street when he was hit 
by a red pickup truck traveling south, Sgt. Michael Harvey said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the truck fled but Javier Ochoa, 22, of Sylmar later called 
police to say he had been involved in the accident, Harvey said. Ochoa was 
arrested at his residence without incident, Harvey said, and was being held in 
lieu of $5,000 bail on suspicion of manslaughter and felony hit-and-run 
driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
